# S13-T6: Time Machine entry point and navigation
# S13-T6-TimeMachineEntryPoint.pd

**Objective:** Provide a clear entry point to the Time Machine view (e.g. route, nav link, or button) and simple navigation: enter Time Machine → see slider + boards at selected time → exit to current view. Integrate with existing app layout and instance context.

**Context:**
- S06: routes /boards, /board/:id. Time Machine can be a new route (e.g. /instances/:id/time-machine or /boards/time-machine?instance=) or a mode toggle on existing boards route. Instance context required so we know which instance's history to show.
- S05/S06: one entry point (link or button), clear exit. No automatic redirect.

**Gate:** OPEN

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. Add entry point: e.g. "Time Machine" link in instance view or boards list header, or a tab. Route to dedicated Time Machine view that includes timeline slider (S13-T3) and boards/tasks at time (S13-T5). Instance id from route or context.
2. Time Machine view layout: slider at top (or side); below it, boards list and board view in read-only mode. "Exit" or "View current" returns to normal boards (current state) and updates route.
3. Ensure deep link or refresh in Time Machine restores selected time if stored in query (e.g. ?at=ISO8601). Optional.
4. Document route and entry in README or S13 invariants. S05/S06 preserved.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- User can open Time Machine from a defined entry point, use the slider to see status at a time, and exit to current view. Instance context and route are clear. S05/S06 preserved.
